post_text:
All K-8 students, both in person and remote learners, take the reading and math Academic Progress (MAP) assessment. In person learners and 5-8 remote learners tested this week. K-4 remote learners will test next week. MAP creates a personalized assessment experience by adapting to each student’s learning level.
Benefits of MAP Assessment:

~Survey Assessment w/ Goals (Students will set goals to monitor progress)
~Aligned to Common Core- matches Limestone placement test for incoming Freshmen
~Information and graphs can be shared during parent/teacher conferences
~Data will help identify gaps within Tier I curriculum/instruction
~Data will help place students into intervention groups based on same instructional needs

post_text: Join us in welcoming Mrs. Bennett, our new Little Flyers preschool teacher! She has been working with preschoolers for nearly 10 years now and has found this career to be the perfect fit for her. She married her husband in 2019 after 12 years together and currently has one dog. Her motto for teaching is to help a child grow into a person they are proud to be and to help build their confidence to try new things. She believes in teaching children through compassion, understanding and letting them explore without the worry of making mistakes. She looks forward to starting this year at Monroe and getting to know everyone!

shared_text:
Monroe Music
May 26 at 11:24 AM ·

To celebrate the end of the school year, for the final chapter of our Quarantine Concert, members of the 6-8 Choir present "You Will Be Found" from the musical "Dear Evan Hansen." This powerful song was picked to be the last song on our Spring Concert to close out the year, and because of the last two months it seems even more powerful. Filmed from their own homes and learned completely on their own (we only had a chance to rehearse this song for ONE DAY prior to the closure), it's a poignant reminder to continue to be creative and expressive even when at home and that we will continue to find ways to rely on and support each other.

post_text:
As a reminder our report card pick up and registration packet drop off is scheduled this week from 6:30 A.M. – 6:30 P.M. each day Tuesday-Friday. If you ordered a yearbook, those will be with report cards. Large envelopes are divided alphabetically by last name and will be available in the vestibule.

There appears to be several students who still have not turned in all items or owe money. Students need to be in good standing to receive report cards. If items still need to be turned in they can be dropped off in the main office from 8:00 a.m. – noon. Do not leave items in the vestibule. Report cards will be held until then.

Students received a grade of pass (CP) or incomplete (CI) due to COVID-19. Since final grades are now completed, we are working on mailing letters to individual students who finished with an incomplete or in danger of failing for the year. The letters will detail summer / fall options to move an incomplete to a passing grade or advancement to the next grade level. We expect letters to be sent the week of June 1st.

Monroe Music
May 7 at 9:13 AM ·

We're back! After some technology delays, the next chapter of our Quarantine Virtual Concert is finally ready! Recorded by the students individually in their own homes, the students use chromebooks, tablets, cell phones, or other devices to record themselves playing along with a track to stay together. Are these virtual performances perfect? No. Do they replicate the experience of making music together all in a room? Of course not. Does it bring joy to see these young musicians still performing together? You bet it does! Enjoy some of the members of the 6-8 Band in their virtual performance of "Arabian Dances" and look for a few more additions to our Quarantine Concert as the school year winds down!

It’s exactly what it sounds like — astronauts on various missions in space read popular children’s books while floating about, and the videos are edited and shared with kids way down on Earth.

Hy-Vee (4125 N Sheridan Rd, Ste 20, Peoria, IL)
UPDATE: Due to the fluid health situation we are all encountering, we need to move our community effort regarding free kids’ lunches to those in need to the school district versus inside our store. We are working with school district officials to donate food for those kids who are in need. We will no longer be holding this operation at our store. If your child needs assistance during this time, please contact masscarepeoriacountyIL@gmail.com, or their Facebook page at Mass Care in Peoria County.
Please know that we want to do everything we can to protect our kids, community and customers during this unusual situation.
We appreciate your understanding!

Friday is a teacher institute with no student attendance. Spring break will stay the same. We will continue to update Monroe families with any changes.
